Ganesh Wall Mask £16.00 http://www.thecuriousemporium.co.uk/ganesh-mask/Ganesh is one of the most widely worshipped deities of the Hindu pantheon. He is the patron of arts and sciences, intellect and wisdom; and he is the remover of obstacles.He is invoked before the beginning of any undertaking, to bless the activity and ensure the success of the task.He is one of the few deities with an animal aspect; and he was said to have been given and Elephant head after his proud mother had instructed all of the gods to gaze in admiration at her son. Including the God Sani; whose gazed burned up everything he cast his gaze upon. Including poor Ganesh head! His mother was then instructed by Brahma, the creator God, to seek out another head and to take the first one she saw. Which happened to be an elephant's head. The second account of Ganesh's story states that his own father Shiva - struck off his head and replaced it with that of an elephant.Although in this mask, he has two tusks he is usually depicted as having only one.One myth states that he lost it during a fight with another God, while another that he himself used it as a pen to write the Mahabharata.This product is approx 7x13 inches. #ganesh   #hindu  ﻿
